g.text: The player finds a book on necromancy - from one of the Red Wizards of Thay. Once read, the book will be bound to whoever tried to read it. Some origins will demand you let them read it, while others will want the book burned. If you read the book, you'll hear strange, distant whispers. The more you read, the stronger the voices will become, and the greater the chance that you'll be driven mad.

g.title: n09ceea0eac691b1755c0b65b2e62bd51
g.text: *You feel its connection. Its longing to be opened - to share its secrets.*

g.title: n2e0ccac6aeec0ae244f513b751d2d507
g.text: *As you look into the book's amethyst eyes, you can almost hear a voice. You just have to open the book, and it will be yours. Forever.*

g.title: na2521ac3cf3db92dd68d7cad79b13392
g.text: *The book is locked tight, with no visible keyhole - only an oval recess in the cover's mouth.*

g.title: nbc293a072d045fa185d5b196e57a6a27
g.text: *The book refuses to open - for you, at least.*

g.title: n005c7962efb064cf2d1a516979c42147
g.text: Well. Quite the page turner. I'll get back to it when I have more time to focus.

g.title: n069248533730bde88e934be5be1e59ca
g.text: *You watch Gale perusing the book with a true wizard's fascination. A few pages in, something startles him.*

g.title: n9f8c26fb299d7d8a65ef5ae9eb530885
g.text: A rough read indeed... I'll give it my undivided attention at a more appropriate time.

g.title: n07c0ed2f2eadde63410c3724da3e499d
g.text: *You try to examine the book, but the longer you stare, the more those piercing, amethyst eyes draw you in.*

g.title: n8e132b386e94d34b3d539ac3e513d60c
g.text: *You feel the darkness radiating from the book. It's delicious.*

g.title: n942cdaa263b8646b250ef0a583db4608
g.text: *You can sense something dark about this tome - something profane.*

g.title: n69025dce6ab36730bc6db0d73a1a7ea8
g.text: *You try to close the book, but claws tear at you from the darkness. You can feel them on your hands, in your eyes, in your soul.*

g.title: n821930dcf7790a8e9cff4ec1e03cb091
g.text: *Glyphs shift gently before your eyes. Words slip into your mind, onto your lips, forming words you don't understand. And

g.title: n09c3c39d0e7d14b56195675a3d70a2aa
g.text: That looks terribly heavy. Why don't you let me carry it for you?

g.title: n916250c10de9378b34dfea5a92026fb1
g.text: *You open the book to the first page, with its shifting glyphs and strange whispers.*

g.title: ndda62d2a05f36af7bcd56643b5c409b7
g.text: *You open the book where you left off, and the voices return, chiding you for your indecision.*

g.title: nfae7529f38f24a0e6694d099567d6c22
g.text: *You open the book where you left off, the glyphs dancing before your eyes.*

g.title: n4e0fe07235526fc562d232475336ec1c
g.text: Please don't open the creepy book.

g.title: n0b01fba57a19c4e787c90d18cb7d03e1
g.text: Drop the tome, ready to destroy it.

g.title: n208308f2964b623bba08b70ee70a1821
g.text: *You feel better the second the book is out of your hands.*

g.title: n6a0ff00b299d43a694acf0ec65cf5a64
g.text: *The glyphs scream, searing your mind. You see time rewritten. Fate undone.*

g.title: n9653abf0744e15eb2b6330cfa1fdfc32
g.text: *The book snaps closed, but that's the least of your worries...*

g.title: nf36721eaf0ebdde73e4c1bcfae7fd6ea
g.text: *The voices return. Louder. Stronger. Commanding you to stop...*

g.title: n205e94538966b52604985a08ac130e9e
g.text: How about you just leave it where you found it, and we saunter away?

g.title: n6467060c8ad0cd8b53b8d0f59041734e
g.text: *You don't know what he read, but it had an effect. His eyes are hungry, but pained.*

g.title: n2b52faa76ab49c1ca9aaad065fcaa8aa
g.text: Place the amethyst in the slot on the book's cover.

g.title: n315204d30c6c534b88f157b882d0e193
g.text: *Black strands of Weave curl all about you, only to sink as into graves as you try to grab hold. Necromantic spells - tantalisingly powerful - slip away forever.*

g.title: n4310f3aff4d34af0ee4a38a94585d991
g.text: *The book snaps closed. You've seen too much. What profane knowledge is now seared inside of you, you should never have known.*

g.title: n33c27c13968c5aa7c9f74155a3e77941
g.text: Enough. Deep into the pack it goes.

g.title: nafffab9fc1b8a8369c9b4666a004dd42
g.text: *The symbols dart beneath your eyes, warping and twisting. Your head throbs, but you almost understand.*

g.title: n39c8fa2a0d04940c1362ffebd17c4eb1
g.text: Turn to the next page, wary of any arcane tricks.

g.title: naa334fbacef92db6a324a7f410c673ed
g.text: *The symbols move aggressively, probing your mental defences, but you hold strong. For now.*

g.title: n402329efea87c15665879f6c472bdd54
g.text: Drink in the darkness, embracing it, and turn the page.

g.title: n406a538d46e519d9e2ac17dd6d0f0587
g.text: *The book slams shut, but the glyphs remain. When you close your eyes, you see them - still glowing in the darkness.*

g.title: n7e7096208c1cbd8a9e843ee1d41dfe4b
g.text: *All you can see are those symbols. All you can hear are the whispers - there is nothing else.*

g.title: n4097507610563636c0428b840de662b3
g.text: *The book sees you in your entirety, and finds you unworthy.*

g.title: n40ebdd2da4948f8c2290179d93cc8d12
g.text: What are you doing? That's no way to treat a book!

g.title: n4151a0fb2145799e85f41fb2d0241242
g.text: *...but they have no hold on you. All you have to do is strike.*

g.title: n42de8989b884d953106bb89da20e9128
g.text: Cast that filth aside. There is little to be learned from scribblings - much less from

g.title: n4368fc4a29f5ea1b3b703d2dfe07ebb2
g.text: That thing is bad news. Hand it here; I'll look after it.

g.title: nbab4488661ec3a2ee410765932667319
g.text: Go on then. Better out than in.

g.title: nbafbe48cd2f3b8e4d05e12f093dd00bf
g.text: *The world around you is gone - you can only see those glyphs, only hear those voices.*

g.title: n52f0c725833f181443ef6f41343cb9a4
g.text: FOR_DangerousBook_State_Bound == False and FOR_DangerousBook_State_BookUnlocked == True and FOR_DangerousBook_GaleWants == True

g.title: n5753c513260a05af7e18de476342c9da
g.text: Tuck the book in your pack.

g.title: n5c3f0913bbec7aab8dabad98cf0da2df
g.text: *You watch her flick through the book, her face tensing as she goes.*

g.title: n9bc1d22cef3ad42957596eba80ecde56
g.text: Urge your hand to turn another page.

g.title: n5e1d2cfddbb273f1df14320bf4c0cff3
g.text: Ask your patron to guard your mind and turn to the next page.

g.title: nc7795c47d7e9e71d2b787778c521b49a
g.text: *The book's pull is irresistable; you feel changed, bettered, for having opened it. Suddenly, you are capable of anything - felling mountains, darkening suns, conversing with the dead.*

g.title: n65650c3745240f34840dd60786cc124a
g.text: *The symbols move aggressively, probing your mental defences. Your patron is there to defend you, but there's only so much they can do.*

g.title: ne86294883c71eeb1f4900fbeb5ed4145
g.text: *The claws try to grip your hands, try to stop you, but you slam the book shut before they can take you.*

g.title: na06252d7c3a9ed0bd629ac2108715360
g.text: I've my fair share of experience with dangerous books. I'll take that off your hands - into more prepared ones.

g.title: nfb638d88ac746882fac16d594344cb10
g.text: A cursed book? How obvious. Whoever opens it deserves the fate that befalls them.

g.title: nde0ea13b18b2d295317895a68068be3d
g.text: You can't be serious. Give it to me this instant!

g.title: nc3421af807bbb30ea6bb547545dc602a
g.text: *Every symbol seems to burn your eyes. You can feel them searing into your mind - into your soul.*

g.title: ne140b11d3bfac8b65dd080ed9c4252cb
g.text: FOR_DangerousBook_State_Bound == False and FOR_DangerousBook_State_BookUnlocked == True and FOR_DangerousBook_HeliaWants == True

g.title: nec49e9454b723c4bd36d6b8a781f7920
g.text: FOR_DangerousBook_AstarionWants == True and FOR_DangerousBook_State_BookUnlocked == True and FOR_DangerousBook_State_Bound == False

g.title: nc70355444f7f98962f09a83dc0f9c482
g.text: *You feel claws moving in the shadows. They pull at you, dragging you closer.*

g.title: nc955353b01146bbd0661c555d2eaf2cd
g.text: Welcome the darkness in the name of your god and turn the page.

g.title: ncdfaea9eda9b958c65efcd066d8f0bf6
g.text: Curious. Why don't you take a closer look... I'll observe from back here.

g.title: nf296f32314280734771b1676b966985c
g.text: Right. It's just... a bit of... hmm.

g.title: nfdfa93139e2239c2a4df6f7c09830d3b
g.text: *The whispers, the pain - it all disappears in an instant. You are yourself again.*
